# AI Instructions

This file is the index of all AI instructions for this repository.

**Before starting any work, re-read all instruction files listed below — they may have changed since your last session.**

**Read and apply ALL of the following instruction files before making any changes:**

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [arch-linux.instructions.md](.github/instructions/arch-linux.instructions.md) | Arch Linux administration, pacman workflows, rolling-release best practices |
| [git-workflow.instructions.md](.github/instructions/git-workflow.instructions.md) | Branching strategy, commit format, PR rules |
| [install-script.instructions.md](.github/instructions/install-script.instructions.md) | Idempotency, script style, shellcheck, scope |
| [docker-compatibility.instructions.md](.github/instructions/docker-compatibility.instructions.md) | Settings that must never break Docker |
| [output-formatting.instructions.md](.github/instructions/output-formatting.instructions.md) | ok / skip / die indicators and colours |
| [changelog.instructions.md](.github/instructions/changelog.instructions.md) | Updating CHANGELOG.md with credfeto.changelog.cmd |

When adding a new rule:
- Add it to the most relevant file in `.github/instructions/`.
- If no existing file fits, create a new `<topic>.instructions.md` file there.
- Update this index table to include any new file.

When you discover something that should be remembered for future work (a tool to use, a pattern to follow, a gotcha to avoid), add it to the most relevant `.github/instructions/` file immediately and include it in the same commit as the change that prompted it.